Subject: [INVITATION] 2012-11-05 - fundiert-entscheiden.de - International =

E-Democracy Talk IV

Hi Folks!

The working group 'AG Meinungsfindungstool' of the Pirate Party Germany
would like to invite you to the 4th International E-Democracy Talk!


WHEN?

Monday, 5th November 2012
Start 9.30pm UTC+1

>> Please be aware that we are back on winter time now <<


WHAT?

Karsten Weihe presents the concept and idea behind the internet portal
"fundiert-entscheiden.de".

  fundiert entscheiden =3D decide on a sound basis
  A collaborative plattform for systematic, factual, to-the-point edition of
controversial questions of all kinds.

Please read the following pdf for more detailed information (german only):
http://dl.dropbox.com/u/52844031/Einf%C3%BChrung%20in%20fundiert-entscheide=
n.de.pdf

For an english version of the conceptual overview please click below:
http://dl.dropbox.com/u/52844031/Poster%20English%20fundiert-entscheiden.de=
.pdf


WHERE?

Server: mumble.piratenpartei-nrw.de
Port: 64738 (standard)
User: <any>
Passwort: <none>
Raum: Bund / Arbeitsgemeinschaften / Technik(IT) / AG Meinungsfindungstool

You don't know Mumble? Click on the link below to learn more:
http://mumble.sourceforge.net/


WHY?

Choose one of the following:

A) Share knowledge to learn from each other.
B) Join forces to upgrade democracy.
C) Prepare for the future.



---
The session is going to be recorded and published for download later.


If you are interessted in our previous talks visit our E-Democracy Talk
Event page:
http://wiki.piratenpartei.de/AG_Meinungsfindungstool/E-democracy_talk#Events

Please note that the page is still under construction!

But if you are interessted in presenting YOUR project, concept or idea at
the next International E-Democray Talk, feel free to sign up and enter your
prefered appointment on the event page. If you are unsure, please create a
doodle poll to schedule the next event.


---
Even if the current time slot may not be optimal for all international
interested parties, we are looking forward hearing you on mumble!


